\begin_layout Description

\emph on
Definition:
\emph default
 A Nash equilibrium (
\begin_inset Quotes els
\end_inset

NE
\begin_inset Quotes ers
\end_inset

) is a strategy profile 
\begin_inset Formula $s^{\ast}$
\end_inset

 such that for every player 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{i}(s_{i}^{\ast},s_{-i}^{\ast})\geq u_{i}(s_{i},s_{-i}^{\ast})$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{i}\in S_{i}.$
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Note how different the NE concept is from the dominant strategy concept:
 the NE concept does not require that 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{i}^{\ast}$
\end_inset

 be dominant for all 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{-i}$
\end_inset

 in 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{-i},$
\end_inset

 but only for 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{-i}^{\ast}$
\end_inset

.
 That is, 
\emph on
taking 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{-i}^{\ast}$
\end_inset

 as given
\emph default
, agent 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 must not strictly prefer to deviate to an action other than 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{i}^{\ast}.$
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

