\begin_layout Description
Nash-Threats
\series medium
 
\series bold
Folk Theorem:
\series default
 Every payoffs within the convex hull that are higher than the Nash equilibrium
 payoff profile for both players can be achieved as a SPNE of the infinitely
 repeated game subject to 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta$
\end_inset

 being high enough.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Remark: Note the proviso that 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta$
\end_inset

 be high enough.
