\begin_layout Standard
Playing 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

 will then be optimal only if in all previous periods both players always
 played 
\begin_inset Formula $C,$
\end_inset

 and if playing 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

 in this period obtains higher payoff than playing 
\begin_inset Formula $D.$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let us see therefore what is the payoff to playing 
\begin_inset Formula $D$
\end_inset

: If one plays 
\begin_inset Formula $D$
\end_inset

 in this period, then one makes 
\begin_inset Formula $7$
\end_inset

